- background
	- Mongoose is a wrapper around MongoDB
	- it enables you to interact with your database simply by using JavaScript objects
	- in this API we are going to an API that performs CRUD operations for a small book website
	- instead of communicating directly with the MongoDB database as we did with [this API](https://edwardtanguay.netlify.app/howtos?id=581)
		- we are going to build a MVC-like abstraction layer between our code and the MongoDB
		- create a **schema and model** for a book
			- a schema defines what fields a book has
			- a model is a schema in a form you can use
		- create book **objects**
			- change these book objects
			- save these book objects
			- Mongoose will take care of all of the communication with the database
	- just as when we used Sequelize (ORM - Object Relational Mapper) which in turn communicated with SQLite and MySQL
		- we will now use Mongoose (ODM - Object Document Mapper) which in turn will communicate with MongoDB
	- full code is here: [edwardtanguay/ejt-howto-mongoose-api](https://github.com/edwardtanguay/ejt-howto-mongoose-api)
		- also, full code to this API together with a frontend Vite site that consumes the API is here: [edwardtanguay/live-coding-ejt-mongoose-book-api](https://github.com/edwardtanguay/live-coding-ejt-mongoose-book-api)##tehbookspapisite
