- **what we will build**
	- we will build a React site with Vite with a simple navbar using React Router
	- we will then build nested navbars four levels deep 
	- we see that React Router has no problem 
		- maintaining URL paths in the browser for these nested site
		- enabling backward and forward browser buttons and browser history
		- when a long URL with many paths is pasted into the browser, React Router will navigate the user directly to that spot in the tree
	- we will show some further features of React Router including
		- highlighting a link in the menu (with `NavLink` instead of `Link`)
		- transfering user one page with another (`Navigate`)
		- inner-site links (`NavLink`)
		- 404 pages (`useLocation`)
		- use `Outlet`
		- URL parameters to identify lookup items on the page, e.g. `store/books/234` (`useParams` and `Outlet`)
		- how to solve the React Router redirect problem on Netlify, Vercel, CloudFlare and self-hosting providers (e.g. `_redirects` file)
