- **what we will build**
	- this project enables developers to create a full-stack backend/frontend CRUD application and deploy it online, but **without yet knowledge of databases or authentication**
	- therefore we need a simplistic database and authentication solution
		- the database is a JSON file accessed by lowdb
		- authentication is simply a PIN stored as environment variable in the backend 
			- the admin will have to identify themselves each time they want to log in, edit or add to the site
	- this howto creates a site
		- that is fullstack with a frontend and backend
		- **ES6 and TypeScript** are in frontend and backend
		- has forms which access a backend API 
		- has CRUD features: add/edit/delete
		- the project is actually a useful site to help anyone search for jobs
		- frontend and backend are hosted on a Debian Linux box at Hetzner
	- we will start with an advanced stage of this project which already shows jobs on the frontend which have a **Delete** button
