	- by default Next.js doesn't seem to have a **src folder**
		- yet a **src folder** is standard in JavaScript framworks, e.g. create-react-app, Vite, Angular, Vue.js
		- and it seems Next.js supports a **src folder** if you want to organize your files that way
			- **"Pages can also be added under src/pages as an alternative to the root pages directory. The src directory is very common in many apps and Next.js supports it by default."* - https://nextjs.org/docs/advanced-features/src-directory
			- apparently this words for the new Next.js 13 **app folder** as well
		- that makes sense to me so that we dont' have files like e.g. **AppContext.tsx** and **interfaces.ts** lying around in the root directory where more typically config files go
		- therefore let's reorganize the folder structure to have a **/src folder**
