		- but now when you add new mixin files, you only need to forward them in the **index.scss** file
			- and you won't have to reference the specific file elsewhere
			- **mixins** is now a namespace that contains all mixins that it forwards

- **the purpose of this howto**
	- we will learn how to use the **BrowserRouter** variant of React Router v6 to accomplish various features, e.g. an item-detail page and a multi-menu page
	- note we will be using the still popular yet older **BrowserRouter** variant of React Router v6
		- it is different than the newer **createBrowserRouter** variant of React Router v6
- **what we will build**
	- we will create a realistic travel website with pages each that show a different feature of the browser:
	- **Welcome page**
		- has deep links to the other pages
	- **Team page**
		- lists out the employees of the company
		- this is an *overview/detail* page
			- `/team` shows all
			- `/team/5` shows employee with id 5
	- **Destination page**
		- shows nested menus of destinations
		- starts with a menu of countries
		- when you click on a country, you get a menu of cities
		- when you click on a city, you get a menu of areas of the city, etc.
	- **Trip Planner page**
		- shows a vertical menu in which you answer questions
		- you keep moving down to more detailed questions
	- here is a rough visual plan of the site:##tehplanfortravel
