- **===== MOST IMPORTANT CONCEPTS, SKILLS AND TOOLS =====**
	- **concepts**
		- **what is the difference between BrowserRouter and createBrowserRouter**
			- they are both variants of React Router v6
			- **BrowserRouter** is older but very widely used
			- **createBrowserRouter** is the newer version
				- supports data loading
				- used as the basis of the **Remix framework**
					- React Router is developed by the Remix team
				- has forward-looking features more compatible with server-side rendering				
	- **skills**
		- **what are the three main steps of setting up a BrowserRouter?**
			- (1) **main.tsx** - wrap the app in BrowserRouter
			- (2) **AppRouter.tsx** - set up the routes
			- (3) **Nav.tsx** - set up the navigation
		- **how to define one of the pages as the landing page if use comes to the base URL**
			- `<Route index element={<Navigate to="/welcome" replace />}/>`
			- this means that if the user comes to the base URL ("index"), they will be redirected ("Navigate") to the welcome page, and this step will not be added in the browser history ("replace")
		- **what do you have to use to make sure the Nav links have "active" classes in them when they are selected**
			- use **NavLink** instead of Link
		- **what do you have to remember to put on your route url for a page that has a submenu**
			- a star, e.g. `<Route path="germany/*" element={<AreaGermany />} />`
	- **tools and commands**
		- npm i react-router-dom
		- BrowserRouter
		- Routes
		- Route
		- NavLink
		- Outlet
