- **background**
	- three common applications that are built with Node are an API, a web server and a CLI
		- an **API** (Application Programming Interface) delivers data and carries out commands via an HTTP port
		- a **web server** delivers HTML that is displayed in a browser
		- a **CLI** (Command-Line Interface) carries out commands typed into the command line, normally by a developer 
- **what will we build**
	- 1. the main purpose of this howto is to show you how to **create a CLI to automate specific tasks** while developing a Vite-React site
		- such as automatically **creating pages and components**
		- e.g. similar to how the Angular CLI enables Angular developers to create pages and components
		- other developers have created similar CLIs for React such as
			- https://www.npmjs.com/package/generate-react-cli
		- however, the advantage of creating our own CLI is that we can **customize it exactly to our needs** or to the needs of any particular project
			- for instance, you might have a project where you need to often perform a particular task such as converting data in an SQL database into JSON files
			- you could use the code base of your CLI to easily create a new command which asked you which table to convert and what the name of the JSON should be, then it would automatically create the JSON file
	- 2. so in this howto you will also learn how to use Node to **create a CLI that can be extended and customized** from project to project in order to automate repetitive tasks and increase your speed as a developer
	- 3. this howto will also show you how to **set up Node to run in the modern programming environment of TypeScript and ES6 modules**
