- **>>> 5. Set up mock CRUD routes for flashcards and test with Postman**
	- we are going to make the most basic routes needed for each item
		- basically this means for teach item (e.g. flashcards) we will have **six routes**:
			- **get all items (GET)**
				- array of items sent back
			- **get one item based on suuid (GET)**
				- item sent back
			- **create a flashcard (POST)**
				- send all fields except suuid which will be created automatically
				- item with newly created suuid sent back
			- **replace all fields except suuid (PUT)**
				- newly changed item sent back
			- **replace one or more fields (PATCH)**
				- newly changed item sent back
			- **delete one item based on suuid (DELETE)**
				- newly deleted item sent back
		- since our CRUD application is only intended to work locally, this will be sufficient
			- since even if we have thousands of items in our collections
				- there will hardly be any speed concerns when sending them all to the frontend and having them queried there
		- but if you want to practice creating routes with more detailed querying possibilities
			- see these [REST API examples and queries](https://restdb.io/docs/querying-with-the-api) 
