					- route level (a specific route)
			- **routing** is the process **creating routes to define and manage the flow of incoming HTTP requests** to specific route handlers, enabling a structured and organized API
			- **error handling** involves **using middleware functions to capture and process errors** that occur during the request-response cycle, improving application robustness by addressing issues and sending appropriate responses to clients 
		- in building our API so far, we have already used all of these to some extent
